As part of Mental Health Awareness month we're sharing this series of Frank conversations about mental health. They're part of Indiana University's fight to end the stigma around mental health that can prevent people from seeking help.

In this edition, Indiana native Ryan Niemiller shares about his journey to becoming a comedian and how he handles stigma associated with his disability.

node.text:
It's Mental Health May and Indiana University is committed to ending the stigma around frank conversations about #mentalhealth. Stigma can be one of the primary barriers to seeking treatment and support for mental health issues, substance use disorder and other health issues.
 Here, @colts Vice Chair/Owner Kalen Jackson discusses her experience with stigma and the campaign the Indianapolis Colts started called, "Kicking the Stigma," which focuses on normalizing the discussion of mental illness and other stigmas the community faces.

#mentalhealthawarenessmonth #mentalhealthmonth #colts #indianapoliscolts #indianauniversity #indianauniversitybloomington #stigma #stigmafree #stigmafighter #iu #iubloomington

node.title: A Conversation With Kalen Jackson: IU Fighting Back Against Stigma

🚨 Don't forget: The opening ceremony for #Tokyo2020 airs tomorrow morning (7/23) from 6:55 to 11 AM eastern on NBC.
